<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="418" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1047,1216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
1. First flagellomere 7.5 × as long as wide; anterior portion of notauli strongly (deeply and widely) impressed; median lobe of mesoscutum with acute corners protruding antero-laterally; nervellus (CU+cu-a) intercepted at its lower third; hind femur 4.6 × as long as wide; face and mesopleuron reddish brown....................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Morley)" baseAuthorityName="Morley" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1234,1437,1106,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Symplecis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petiolata">
<emphasis box="[1234,1343,1106,1127]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">S. petiolata</emphasis>
(Morley)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1047,1216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
– First flagellomere 5.6 × as long as wide; anterior portion of notauli not strongly impressed; median lobe of mesoscutum without corners protruding antero-laterally (
<figureCitation box="[569,643,1164,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-200@5.[189,1398,525,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Symplecis anaeratabettensis sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head, antero-ventral view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma (in part), dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683448/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); nervellus (CU+cu-a) not intercepted; hind femur 5.8 × as long as wide; face pale, mesopleuron yellow (
<figureCitation box="[434,540,1194,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-200@5.[189,1398,525,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Symplecis anaeratabettensis sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head, antero-ventral view; E) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; F) mesosoma (in part), dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683448/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Figs 3A, E</figureCitation>
